cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of constructing 4-connected triangulations of planar point sets, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and geometric graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also presents an algorithm for constructing the triangulation, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also discusses the structure of the triangulation, which involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GR (Graph Theory) likely categories. Finally, the paper presents a necessary and sufficient condition for recognizing the point set, which involves computational complexity, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible category as well.
